# Book: Daniel

# Section: In the third year of the reign of Jehoiakim king of Judah
# Daniel 01:01
STARTHERE

In the third year of the reign of Jehoiakim king of Judah,
Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came to Jerusalem and besieged it.

# Daniel 01:02
The Lord gave Jehoiakim king of Judah into his hand,
with some of the vessels of the house of God;
and he carried them into the land of Shinar to the house of his god.

He brought the vessels into the treasure house of his god.

# Daniel 01:03
The king spoke to Ashpenaz,
the master of his eunuchs,
that he should bring in some of the children of Israel,
even of the royal offspring and of the nobles:

# Daniel 01:04
youths in whom was no defect,
but well-favored,
skillful in all wisdom,
endowed with knowledge,
understanding science,
and who had the ability to stand in the king's palace;
and that he should teach them the learning and the language of the Chaldeans.

# Daniel 01:05
The king appointed for them a daily portion of the king's delicacies and of the wine which he drank,
and that they should be nourished three years,
that at its end they should stand before the king.

# Daniel 01:06
Now among these of the children of Judah were Daniel,
Hananiah,
Mishael,
and Azariah.

# Daniel 01:07
The prince of the eunuchs gave names to them:
to Daniel he gave the name Belteshazzar;
to Hananiah,
Shadrach;
to Mishael,
Meshach;
and to Azariah,
Abednego.

# Daniel 01:08
But Daniel purposed in his heart that he would not defile himself with the king's delicacies,
nor with the wine which he drank.

Therefore he requested of the prince of the eunuchs that he might not defile himself.

# Daniel 01:09
Now God made Daniel find kindness and compassion in the sight of the prince of the eunuchs.

# Daniel 01:10
The prince of the eunuchs said to Daniel,
``I fear my lord the king,
who has appointed your food and your drink.

For why should he see your faces worse looking than the youths who are of your own age?

Then you would endanger my head with the king.''

# Daniel 01:11
Then Daniel said to the steward whom the prince of the eunuchs had appointed over Daniel,
Hananiah,
Mishael,
and Azariah:

# Daniel 01:12
``Test your servants,
I beg you,
ten days;
and let them give us vegetables to eat and water to drink.

# Daniel 01:13
Then let our faces be examined before you,
and the face of the youths who eat of the king's delicacies;
and as you see,
deal with your servants.''

# Daniel 01:14
So he listened to them in this matter,
and tested them for ten days.

# Daniel 01:15
At the end of ten days,
their faces appeared fairer and they were fatter in flesh than all the youths who ate of the king's delicacies.

# Daniel 01:16
So the steward took away their delicacies and the wine that they were given to drink,
and gave them vegetables.

# Daniel 01:17
Now as for these four youths,
God gave them knowledge and skill in all learning and wisdom;
and Daniel had understanding in all visions and dreams.

# Daniel 01:18
At the end of the days which the king had appointed for bringing them in,
the prince of the eunuchs brought them in before Nebuchadnezzar.

# Daniel 01:19
The king talked with them;
and among them all was found no one like Daniel,
Hananiah,
Mishael,
and Azariah.

Therefore stood they before the king.

# Daniel 01:20
In every matter of wisdom and understanding concerning which the king inquired of them,
he found them ten times better than all the magicians and enchanters who were in all his realm.

# Daniel 01:21
Daniel continued even to the first year of King Cyrus.

# Daniel 01:22
Daniel.

# Daniel 02:01
In the second year of the reign of Nebuchadnezzar,
Nebuchadnezzar dreamed dreams;
and his spirit was troubled,
and his sleep went from him.

# Daniel 02:02
Then the king commanded that the magicians,
the enchanters,
the sorcerers,
and the Chaldeans be called to tell the king his dreams.

So they came in and stood before the king.

# Daniel 02:03
The king said to them,
``I have dreamed a dream,
and my spirit is troubled to know the dream.''

# Daniel 02:04
Then the Chaldeans spoke to the king in the Syrian language,
``O king,
live forever!

Tell your servants the dream,
and we will show the interpretation.''

# Daniel 02:05
The king answered the Chaldeans,
``The thing has gone from me.

If you don’t make known to me the dream and its interpretation,
you will be cut in pieces,
and your houses will be made a dunghill.

# Daniel 02:06
But if you show the dream and its interpretation,
you will receive from me gifts,
rewards,
and great honor.

Therefore show me the dream and its interpretation.''

# Daniel 02:07
They answered the second time and said,
``Let the king tell his servants the dream,
and we will show the interpretation.''

# Daniel 02:08
The king answered,
``I know of a certainty that you are trying to gain time,
because you see the thing has gone from me.

# Daniel 02:09
But if you don’t make known to me the dream,
there is but one law for you;
