lord,
or ruler has asked such a thing of any magician,
enchanter,
or Chaldean.

# Daniel 02:11
It is a rare thing that the king requires,
and there is no other who can show it before the king except the gods,
whose dwelling is not with flesh.''

# Daniel 02:12
Because of this,
the king was angry and very furious,
and commanded that all the wise men of Babylon be destroyed.

# Daniel 02:13
So the decree went out,
and the wise men were to be slain.

They sought Daniel and his companions to be slain.

# Daniel 02:14
Then Daniel returned answer with counsel and prudence to Arioch the captain of the king's guard,
who had gone out to kill the wise men of Babylon.

# Daniel 02:15
He answered Arioch the king's captain,
``Why is the decree so urgent from the king?''

Then Arioch made the thing known to Daniel.

# Daniel 02:16
Daniel went in,
and desired of the king that he would appoint him a time,
and he would show the king the interpretation.

# Daniel 02:17
Then Daniel went to his house and made the thing known to Hananiah,
Mishael,
and Azariah,
his companions:

# Daniel 02:18
that they would desire mercies of the God of heaven concerning this secret,
that Daniel and his companions would not perish with the rest of the wise men of Babylon.

# Daniel 02:19
Then the secret was revealed to Daniel in a vision of the night.

Then Daniel blessed the God of heaven.

# Daniel 02:20
Daniel answered,
``Blessed be the name of God forever and ever;
