and said this to him:
``I have found a man of the children of the captivity of Judah who will make known to the king the interpretation.''

# Daniel 02:26
The king answered Daniel,
whose name was Belteshazzar,
``Are you able to make known to me the dream which I have seen,
and its interpretation?''

# Daniel 02:27
Daniel answered before the king,
and said,
``The secret which the king has demanded can’t be shown to the king by wise men,
enchanters,
magicians,
or soothsayers;

# Daniel 02:28
but there is a God in heaven who reveals secrets,
and he has made known to King Nebuchadnezzar what will be in the latter days.

Your dream and the visions of your head on your bed are these:

# Daniel 02:29
``As for you,
O king,
